PrettyB plot.default function

Source: R/plot.R
plot.prettyB.Rd

This function overrides the default arguments. See ?graphics::plot.default

# S3 method for prettyB
plot(
  x,
  y = NULL,
  type = "p",
  xlim = NULL,
  ylim = NULL,
  log = "",
  main = NULL,
  sub = NULL,
  xlab = NULL,
  ylab = NULL,
  ann = par("ann"),
  axes = TRUE,
  frame.plot = axes,
  panel.first = NULL,
  panel.last = NULL,
  asp = NA,
  ...
)

plot_p(
  x,
  y = NULL,
  type = "p",
  xlim = NULL,
  ylim = NULL,
  log = "",
  main = NULL,
  sub = NULL,
  xlab = NULL,
  ylab = NULL,
  ann = par("ann"),
  axes = TRUE,
  frame.plot = axes,
  panel.first = NULL,
  panel.last = NULL,
  asp = NA,
  ...
)

x, y, type, log

See ?graphics::plot.default
